The article is a letter from the President of the United States to the Speaker of the House, providing a report on the military operations and deployments of U.S. Armed Forces. The report focuses on operations against al-Qa'ida, the Taliban, and associated forces in Afghanistan, as well as efforts in Somalia and Yemen to counter the terrorist threat posed by these groups. It also mentions the completion of military operations in Iraq and the deployment of U.S. military personnel to Central Africa to assist in efforts against the Lord's Resistance Army. The letter emphasizes the commitment to protecting U.S. citizens and interests from terrorist threats and the ongoing cooperation with international partners in these efforts. It also mentions the participation of U.S. Armed Forces in maritime interception operations and the successful hostage rescue operation in Somalia. The letter concludes by stating that these deployments are carried out under the President's constitutional and statutory authority as Commander in Chief and Chief Executive, and that regular communication with Congress will continue.